In this program, we will take a list of characters as input and modify the list such that all consecutive duplicate characters are removed, leaving only one instance of each character. If there are multiple consecutive duplicate characters, only one instance of the character will be kept.

We will iterate through the input list and compare each character with the previous one. If the current character is the same as the previous one, we will continue to the next character. If the current character is different from the previous one, we will add it to the output list.

Finally, the output list will contain the modified sequence with consecutive duplicate characters removed.

The time complexity of this algorithm is O(n) where n is the number of characters in the input list. This is because we only iterate through the list once to remove consecutive duplicates.
